snippet: On Wednesday, the spacecraft that has studied Saturn for a dozen years will commence a series of maneuvers that will graze the planet’s rings....
abstract: NASA's Cassini spacecraft is set to travel to outer edge of Saturn's ring system to collect ring particles and gases.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, the spacecraft that has studied Saturn for a dozen years will commence a series of maneuvers that will graze the planet’s rings.

headline.print_headline: End Days: NASA’s Cassini Nears End of Saturn Mission
headline.main: How Cassini Will Begin Its Date With Death on Saturn
